{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862584897,"sessionID":"ses_28657a10effeJg2rEsldi5zbr1","part":{"id":"prt_d79a88c7a0012i26mCveWVjrep","messageID":"msg_d79a880bc001KYT5XLGFoLMBaN","sessionID":"ses_28657a10effeJg2rEsldi5zbr1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_81b1710e4daa4acf8160fc7d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: PicoD File Management API (AR-016)\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement the file management API for the PicoD module in `pkg/picod`, providing secure file operations within sandboxed environments including read, write, list, and delete capabilities with proper security validations and resource limits.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: The PicoD File Management API provides:\n12: \n13: 1. **Secure File Operations**: Read, write, list, and delete files within controlled sandbox directories\n14: 2. **Path Validation**: Ensure all file operations stay within allowed workspace boundaries\n15: 3. **Resource Limits**: Enforce file size limits, directory depth limits, and quota management\n16: 4. **Atomic Operations**: Support for atomic write operations to prevent partial writes\n17: 5. **Metadata Access**: Retrieve file metadata (size, modification time, permissions)\n18: \n19: This implementation builds upon the command execution infrastructure from AR-015 and provides the file management layer needed for code interpreters and agent runtimes to interact with the filesystem safely.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Scope\n24: \n25: ### In Scope\n26: \n27: - `pkg/picod/filesystem.go` - File operations interface and implementation\n28: - `pkg/picod/fileinfo.go` - File metadata and information structures\n29: - `pkg/picod/quota.go` - Disk quota management and enforcement\n30: - `pkg/picod/path.go` - Path validation and normalization utilities\n31: - `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go` - File operation unit tests\n32: - `pkg/picod/quota_test.go` - Quota management tests\n33: - `pkg/picod/path_test.go` - Path validation tests\n34: - `pkg/picod/integration_test.go` - Integration tests (extended)\n35: \n36: ### Out of Scope\n37: \n38: - Network filesystem support (NFS, SMB, etc.)\n39: - File watching/notification systems\n40: - Advanced permissions (ACLs, extended attributes)\n41: - File encryption/decryption\n42: - Distributed file locking\n43: - Backup and snapshot functionality\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## Impact Analysis\n48: \n49: ### Dependencies\n50: \n51: | Package | Purpose |\n52: |---------|---------|\n53: | `os` | File operations and metadata |\n54: | `io` | Stream operations |\n55: | `io/fs` | Filesystem interfaces |\n56: | `path/filepath` | Path manipulation |\n57: | `context` | Operation cancellation and timeouts |\n58: | `syscall` | Low-level filesystem operations |\n59: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n60: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` | Existing PicoD types and limits |\n61: \n62: ### Affected Components\n63: \n64: 1. **Code Interpreter**: Will use file API for reading/writing code files and outputs\n65: 2. **Agent Runtime**: Will use file API for accessing configuration and state files\n66: 3. **Workload Manager**: Will use file API for managing job artifacts\n67: 4. **Sandbox Manager**: Will configure filesystem quotas and permissions\n68: 5. **Security Module**: Will validate file operation permissions\n69: \n70: ### Backward Compatibility\n71: \n72: - This is a new API surface within the existing PicoD module\n73: - No breaking changes to existing AR-015 command execution APIs\n74: - Extends PicoD struct with additional methods\n75: - Configuration via environment variables and programmatic API\n76: \n77: ### Risk Assessment\n78: \n79: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n80: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n81: | Path traversal attack | Medium | Critical | Strict path validation, chroot-style isolation |\n82: | Disk space exhaustion | High | High | Enforce quotas, validate write sizes |\n83: | Symlink attacks | Medium | High | Resolve and validate symlink targets |\n84: | Race conditions | Medium | Medium | Atomic operations where possible, proper locking |\n85: | Information disclosure | Low | High | Validate read operations, enforce permissions |\n86: | Directory depth attacks | Low | Medium | Enforce maximum directory depth limits |\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## Alternatives Considered\n91: \n92: ### Alternative 1: Use os.* Directly\n93: \n94: **Approach**: Expose standard library `os` package functions directly\n95: \n96: **Pros**:\n97: - Minimal implementation effort\n98: - No additional abstraction layer\n99: - Full control for callers\n100: \n101: **Cons**:\n102: - No security enforcement\n103: - No quota management\n104: - Easy to misuse\n105: - Hard to audit file operations\n106: \n107: **Decision**: Wrap with security and quota validation layer.\n108: \n109: ### Alternative 2: In-Memory Filesystem (afero)\n110: \n111: **Approach**: Use afero or similar in-memory filesystem abstraction\n112: \n113: **Pros**:\n114: - Easy testing and mocking\n115: - Built-in abstraction layer\n116: - Additional safety\n117: \n118: **Cons**:\n119: - Additional dependency\n120: - Doesn't match real filesystem behavior exactly\n121: - May not support all operations needed\n122: \n123: **Decision**: Use real filesystem with validation for production accuracy.\n124: \n125: ### Alternative 3: Container-mounted Volumes\n126: \n127: **Approach**: Delegate file operations to container runtime volume mounts\n128: \n129: **Pros**:\n130: - Leverages container isolation\n131: - No additional code to maintain\n132: - Clear security boundary\n133: \n134: **Cons**:\n135: - Requires container runtime integration\n136: - Less flexible for non-container deployments\n137: - More complex orchestration\n138: \n139: **Decision**: Implement native file operations; container integration can be added later.\n140: \n141: ---\n142: \n143: ## Implementation Details\n144: \n145: ### File Quota\n146: \n147: ```go\n148: type FileQuota struct {\n149:     // MaxFileSize is the maximum size of a single file in bytes\n150:     MaxFileSize int64\n151:     \n152:     // MaxTotalSize is the maximum total size of all files in bytes\n153:     MaxTotalSize int64\n154:     \n155:     // MaxFiles is the maximum number of files allowed\n156:     MaxFiles int64\n157:     \n158:     // MaxDirectoryDepth is the maximum directory depth\n159:     MaxDirectoryDepth int\n160: }\n161: ```\n162: \n163: ### FileInfo\n164: \n165: ```go\n166: type FileInfo struct {\n167:     // Name is the file name\n168:     Name string\n169:     \n170:     // Path is the full path within the sandbox\n171:     Path string\n172:     \n173:     // Size is the file size in bytes\n174:     Size int64\n175:     \n176:     // Mode is the file mode and permissions\n177:     Mode os.FileMode\n178:     \n179:     // ModTime is the last modification time\n180:     ModTime time.Time\n181:     \n182:     // IsDir indicates if this is a directory\n183:     IsDir bool\n184:     \n185:     // FileType indicates the file type (regular, symlink, etc.)\n186:     FileType FileType\n187: }\n188: \n189: type FileType string\n190: \n191: const (\n192:     FileTypeRegular   FileType = \"regular\"\n193:     FileTypeDirectory FileType = \"directory\"\n194:     FileTypeSymlink   FileType = \"symlink\"\n195:     FileTypeOther     FileType = \"other\"\n196: )\n197: ```\n198: \n199: ### File Operations Interface\n200: \n201: ```go\n202: type FileSystem interface {\n203:     // Read reads the entire contents of a file\n204:     Read(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]byte, error)\n205:     \n206:     // ReadStream reads a file with streaming support\n207:     ReadStream(ctx context.Context, path string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n208:     \n209:     // Write writes data to a file atomically\n210:     Write(ctx context.Context, path string, data []byte) error\n211:     \n212:     // WriteStream writes from a stream with size limit\n213:     WriteStream(ctx context.Context, path string, reader io.Reader, size int64) error\n214:     \n215:     // Delete removes a file or empty directory\n216:     Delete(ctx context.Context, path string) error\n217:     \n218:     // DeleteAll removes a directory and all contents\n219:     DeleteAll(ctx context.Context, path string) error\n220:     \n221:     // Exists checks if a path exists\n222:     Exists(ctx context.Context, path string) (bool, error)\n223:     \n224:     // Info returns file metadata\n225:     Info(ctx context.Context, path string) (*FileInfo, error)\n226:     \n227:     // List lists directory contents\n228:     List(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]FileInfo, error)\n229:     \n230:     // Mkdir creates a directory\n231:     Mkdir(ctx context.Context, path string, perm os.FileMode) error\n232:     \n233:     // MkdirAll creates a directory and all parent directories\n234:     MkdirAll(ctx context.Context, path string, perm os.FileMode) error\n235:     \n236:     // Rename renames/moves a file or directory\n237:     Rename(ctx context.Context, oldPath, newPath string) error\n238:     \n239:     // Copy copies a file\n240:     Copy(ctx context.Context, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n241:     \n242:     // Quota returns current quota usage\n243:     Quota(ctx context.Context) (*QuotaUsage, error)\n244: }\n245: ```\n246: \n247: ### Quota Usage\n248: \n249: ```go\n250: type QuotaUsage struct {\n251:     // UsedBytes is the total bytes used\n252:     UsedBytes int64\n253:     \n254:     // MaxBytes is the maximum bytes allowed\n255:     MaxBytes int64\n256:     \n257:     // FileCount is the number of files\n258:     FileCount int64\n259:     \n260:     // MaxFiles is the maximum files allowed\n261:     MaxFiles int64\n262:     \n263:     // PercentUsed is the percentage of quota used (0-100)\n264:     PercentUsed float64\n265: }\n266: ```\n267: \n268: ### PicoD Integration\n269: \n270: ```go\n271: // PicoD struct extended with filesystem\n272: type PicoD struct {\n273:     sandboxID    string\n274:     workDir      string\n275:     limits       *ResourceLimits\n276:     securityOpts *SecurityOptions\n277:     fileQuota    *FileQuota\n278:     logger       klog.Logger\n279:     \n280:     // File system operations\n281:     fs FileSystem\n282: }\n283: \n284: // FileSystem returns the file system interface\n285: func (p *PicoD) FileSystem() FileSystem\n286: \n287: // Convenience methods on PicoD\n288: func (p *PicoD) ReadFile(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]byte, error)\n289: func (p *PicoD) WriteFile(ctx context.Context, path string, data []byte) error\n290: func (p *PicoD) ListDir(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]FileInfo, error)\n291: func (p *PicoD) DeleteFile(ctx context.Context, path string) error\n292: func (p *PicoD) GetQuota(ctx context.Context) (*QuotaUsage, error)\n293: ```\n294: \n295: ### Path Validation\n296: \n297: ```go\n298: // ValidatePath validates a path is within the workspace\n299: func ValidatePath(path, workDir string) (string, error)\n300: \n301: // ResolvePath resolves a path to absolute, following symlinks\n302: func ResolvePath(path string) (string, error)\n303: \n304: // GetDepth returns the directory depth of a path\n305: func GetDepth(path string) int\n306: \n307: // IsWithinWorkspace checks if resolved path is within workspace\n308: func IsWithinWorkspace(path, workDir string) bool\n309: ```\n310: \n311: ### Atomic Write Implementation\n312: \n313: ```go\n314: // Write atomically writes data to a file\n315: func (fs *fileSystem) Write(ctx context.Context, path string, data []byte) error {\n316:     // 1. Validate path\n317:     absPath, err := ValidatePath(path, fs.workDir)\n318:     if err != nil {\n319:         return err\n320:     }\n321:     \n322:     // 2. Check quota\n323:     if int64(len(data)) > fs.quota.MaxFileSize {\n324:         return &FileError{\n325:             Type:    FileErrorQuotaExceeded,\n326:             Message: \"file size exceeds quota\",\n327:         }\n328:     }\n329:     \n330:     // 3. Write to temporary file\n331:     tmpPath := absPath + \".tmp.\" + uuid()\n332:     if err := os.WriteFile(tmpPath, data, 0644); err != nil {\n333:         return &FileError{\n334:             Type:    FileErrorWrite,\n335:             Message: \"failed to write file\",\n336:             Underlying: err,\n337:         }\n338:     }\n339:     \n340:     // 4. Atomic rename\n341:     if err := os.Rename(tmpPath, absPath); err != nil {\n342:         os.Remove(tmpPath) // Cleanup\n343:         return &FileError{\n344:             Type:    FileErrorWrite,\n345:             Message: \"failed to rename file\",\n346:             Underlying: err,\n347:         }\n348:     }\n349:     \n350:     return nil\n351: }\n352: ```\n353: \n354: ---\n355: \n356: ## Configuration Reference\n357: \n358: ### Environment Variables\n359: \n360: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n361: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n362: | `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_FILE_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Maximum single file size |\n363: | `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_TOTAL_SIZE` | No | `100MB` | Maximum total storage |\n364: | `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_FILES` | No | `1000` | Maximum number of files |\n365: | `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_DEPTH` | No | `10` | Maximum directory depth |\n366: | `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n367: \n368: ### Example Configuration\n369: \n370: ```go\n371: quota := &FileQuota{\n372:     MaxFileSize:       10 * 1024 * 1024,  // 10 MiB\n373:     MaxTotalSize:      100 * 1024 * 1024, // 100 MiB\n374:     MaxFiles:          1000,\n375:     MaxDirectoryDepth: 10,\n376: }\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ---\n380: \n381: ## Testing Strategy\n382: \n383: ### Unit Tests\n384: \n385: | Test | Purpose |\n386: |------|---------|\n387: | `TestFileSystem_Read_Success` | Basic file read |\n388: | `TestFileSystem_Read_NotFound` | Read non-existent file |\n389: | `TestFileSystem_Read_PathTraversal` | Path traversal blocked |\n390: | `TestFileSystem_Write_Success` | Basic file write |\n391: | `TestFileSystem_Write_Atomic` | Atomic write verification |\n392: | `TestFileSystem_Write_QuotaExceeded` | Write exceeds quota |\n393: | `TestFileSystem_Delete_Success` | Delete file |\n394: | `TestFileSystem_Delete_All` | Delete directory recursively |\n395: | `TestFileSystem_Exists` | Check file existence |\n396: | `TestFileSystem_Info` | Get file metadata |\n397: | `TestFileSystem_List` | List directory contents |\n398: | `TestFileSystem_Mkdir` | Create directories |\n399: | `TestFileSystem_Rename` | Rename/move files |\n400: | `TestFileSystem_Copy` | Copy files |\n401: | `TestFileSystem_Quota` | Quota usage tracking |\n402: | `TestValidatePath_Success` | Valid paths accepted |\n403: | `TestValidatePath_PathTraversal` | Path traversal rejected |\n404: | `TestValidatePath_Symlink` | Symlink validation |\n405: | `TestGetDepth` | Directory depth calculation |\n406: \n407: ### Integration Tests\n408: \n409: | Test | Purpose |\n410: |------|---------|\n411: | `TestFileSystem_Integration_FullLifecycle` | Full file operation lifecycle |\n412: | `TestFileSystem_Integration_Concurrent` | Concurrent file operations |\n413: | `TestFileSystem_Integration_QuotaEnforcement` | Verify quotas are enforced |\n414: | `TestFileSystem_Integration_AtomicWrite` | Atomic write under load |\n415: | `TestFileSystem_Integration_LargeFiles` | Handle files near size limit |\n416: \n417: ### Test Fixtures\n418: \n419: ```go\n420: // mockFileSystem creates a test file system\n421: func mockFileSystem(t *testing.T, quota *FileQuota) (FileSystem, func()) {\n422:     tmpDir := t.TempDir()\n423:     fs := NewFileSystem(tmpDir, quota, klog.Background())\n424:     cleanup := func() {}\n425:     return fs, cleanup\n426: }\n427: \n428: // createTestFile creates a test file with given size\n429: func createTestFile(fs FileSystem, path string, size int64) error {\n430:     data := make([]byte, size)\n431:     for i := range data {\n432:         data[i] = byte(i % 256)\n433:     }\n434:     return fs.Write(context.Background(), path, data)\n435: }\n436: ```\n437: \n438: ---\n439: \n440: ## Acceptance Criteria\n441: \n442: - [ ] `FileSystem` interface implements all required methods\n443: - [ ] Path validation prevents operations outside workspace\n444: - [ ] Quota enforcement works correctly (size, file count, depth)\n445: - [ ] Atomic writes prevent partial file corruption\n446: - [ ] Symlink attacks are prevented\n447: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n448: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n449: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n450: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n451: - [ ] Error types are properly classified and documented\n452: - [ ] File operations are logged for audit trail\n453: \n454: ---\n455: \n456: ## Error Handling\n457: \n458: ### FileError\n459: \n460: ```go\n461: type FileError struct {\n462:     Type       FileErrorType\n463:     Message    string\n464:     Underlying error\n465: }\n466: \n467: type FileErrorType string\n468: \n469: const (\n470:     FileErrorNotFound      FileErrorType = \"not_found\"\n471:     FileErrorPermission    FileErrorType = \"permission\"\n472:     FileErrorQuotaExceeded FileErrorType = \"quota_exceeded\"\n473:     FileErrorPathTraversal FileErrorType = \"path_traversal\"\n474:     FileErrorWrite         FileErrorType = \"write\"\n475:     FileErrorRead          FileErrorType = \"read\"\n476:     FileErrorSymlink       FileErrorType = \"symlink\"\n477:     FileErrorDepth         FileErrorType = \"depth_exceeded\"\n478: )\n479: ```\n480: \n481: ### Error Conditions\n482: \n483: | Condition | Error Type | HTTP Mapping | Description |\n484: |-----------|------------|--------------|-------------|\n485: | File does not exist | `FileErrorNotFound` | 404 Not Found | Requested file was not found |\n486: | Path outside workspace | `FileErrorPathTraversal` | 403 Forbidden | Path validation failed |\n487: | Quota exceeded | `FileErrorQuotaExceeded` | 413 Payload Too Large | File/quota limit exceeded |\n488: | Permission denied | `FileErrorPermission` | 403 Forbidden | Insufficient permissions |\n489: | Symlink attack | `FileErrorSymlink` | 403 Forbidden | Symlink target outside workspace |\n490: | Directory depth exceeded | `FileErrorDepth` | 400 Bad Request | Path exceeds max depth |\n491: | Write failure | `FileErrorWrite` | 500 Internal Server Error | Failed to write file |\n492: | Read failure | `FileErrorRead` | 500 Internal Server Error | Failed to read file |\n493: \n494: ---\n495: \n496: ## References\n497: \n498: - AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n499: - AR-012: Sandbox Infrastructure\n500: - `pkg/picod/design.md`: PicoD Design Document\n501: - `pkg/picod/tasks.md`: PicoD Task List (AR-015)\n502: - `code-execution/spec.md`: PicoD Specification\n\n(End of file - total 502 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: PicoD File Management API (AR-016)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the file management API for the PicoD module in `pkg/picod`, providing secure file operations within sandboxed environments including read, write, list, and delete capabilities with proper security validations and resource limits.\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe PicoD File Management API provides:\n\n1. **Secure File Operations**: Read, write, list, and delete files within controlled sandbox directories\n2. **Path Validation**: Ensure all file operations stay within allowed workspace boundaries\n3. **Resource Limits**: Enforce file size limits, directory depth limits, and quota management\n4. **Atomic Operations**: Support for atomic write operations to prevent partial writes\n5. **Metadata Access**: Retrieve file metadata (size, modification time, permissions)\n\nThis implementation builds upon the command execution infrastructure from AR-015 and provides the file management layer needed for code interpreters and agent runtimes to interact with the filesystem safely.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775862584867,"end":1775862584894}}}}
