{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862721403,"sessionID":"ses_28657a10effeJg2rEsldi5zbr1","part":{"id":"prt_d79a92133001ZAkdJawNZK3B7F","messageID":"msg_d79a91554001h4FR2Bztw8jwBA","sessionID":"ses_28657a10effeJg2rEsldi5zbr1","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_a4b0599fb43d4c08a7c7936b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller (AR-018)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement an idle cleanup controller in `pkg/agentd` that automatically identifies and terminates idle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources based on configurable inactivity timeouts, releasing cluster resources and maintaining system hygiene.\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller provides:\n\n1. **Resource Reclamation**: Automatically clean up idle agent runtimes and code interpreters to free cluster resources\n2. **Configurable Idle Detection**: Support per-resource-type idle timeout configuration\n3. **Graceful Termination**: Properly finalize resources before deletion with status updates\n4. **Observability**: Emit metrics and logs for cleanup operations\n5. **Safe Operation**: Respect resource11s and avoid cleaning resources with active workloads\n\nThis implementation builds upon the client-go infrastructure from `deployment/client-go.md` and integrates with the workload manager's reconciliation loop to ensure cleaned resources are properly handled.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n- `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` - Idle cleanup controller interface and implementation\n- `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go` - Idle state tracking and timeout detection\n- `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go` - Metrics for cleanup operations\n- `pkg/agentd/config.go` - Configuration for idle timeouts and cleanup behavior\n- `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go` - Unit tests for cleanup logic\n- `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker_test.go` - Unit tests for idle detection\n- `pkg/agentd/integration_test.go` - Integration tests with fake clients\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Manual termination APIs (covered by workload manager handlers)\n- Resource scaling policies (future AR)\n- Cross-namespace cleanup coordination\n- Custom resource definition modifications\n- User notification systems for impending cleanup\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Kubernetes client interface |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | Metadata and deletion options |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/watch` | Watch interface for resource monitoring |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n| `prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` | Metrics exposition |\n| `golang.org/x/sync/errgroup` | Concurrent cleanup operations |\n\n### Affected Components\n\n1. **Workload Manager**: Receives deletion events for cleaned resources; must handle graceful termination\n2. **Reconciler**: Processes status updates from cleanup operations; updates finalizers\n3. **Metrics System**: Exposes cleanup metrics for monitoring dashboards\n4. **Router Session Manager**: May need to invalidate sessions for cleaned resources\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- This is a new controller within agentd\n- No breaking changes to existing APIs\n- Configuration via environment variables with sensible defaults\n- Can be disabled via configuration flag\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Premature cleanup of active resources | Low | High | Conservative idle detection, last-activity tracking from workload manager |\n| Cleanup storm under load | Medium | Medium | Rate limiting, concurrent cleanup limits |\n| Resource leak if cleanup fails | Medium | Medium | Retry logic, metrics for failed cleanups |\n| Watch connection failures | Medium | Low | Exponential backoff, periodic full scans |\n| Namespace isolation violations | Low | High | Namespace-scoped clients, validation |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: TTL-Based Kubernetes Finalizers\n\n**Approach**: Use Kubernetes native TTL secondsAfterFinished on resources\n\n**Pros**:\n- Leverages Kubernetes garbage collection\n- No additional controller logic needed\n- Native integration with Kubernetes lifecycle\n\n**Cons**:\n- Requires CRD modifications\n- Only triggers after completion, not for idle resources\n- Less flexible timeout configuration\n\n**Decision**: Implement custom idle detection for more granular control.\n\n### Alternative 2: Workload Manager Integrated Cleanup\n\n**Approach**: Add cleanup logic directly to workload manager reconciliation loop\n\n**Pros**:\n- Single reconciliation loop\n- Direct access to workload state\n- No inter-controller coordination\n\n**Cons**:\n- Bloated reconciliation logic\n- Cleanup delays during high reconciliation load\n- Harder to tune cleanup independently\n\n**Decision**: Separate controller for cleaner separation of concerns and independent tuning.\n\n### Alternative 3: CronJob-Based Cleanup\n\n**Approach**: Deploy cleanup logic as periodic Kubernetes CronJob\n\n**Pros**:\n- Simple to understand and deploy\n- Kubernetes-native scheduling\n- No long-running process\n\n**Cons**:\n- No real-time idle detection\n- Potential race conditions with concurrent runs\n- Less responsive to load changes\n\n**Decision**: Continuous controller for better responsiveness and state tracking.\n\n### Alternative 4: Label-Based Selection\n\n**Approach**: Use label selectors to mark resources for cleanup, separate finalizer processes them\n\n**Pros**:\n- Clear separation of detection and execution\n- Audit trail via labels\n- Easier debugging\n\n**Cons**:\n- Additional API surface (label management)\n- More complex state machine\n- Label cleanup required\n\n**Decision**: Direct deletion for simpler implementation; can add labels later for audit.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### IdleCleanupController Interface\n\n```go\ntype IdleCleanupController interface {\n    // Start starts the idle cleanup controller\n    Start(ctx context.Context) error\n    \n    // Stop stops the controller gracefully\n    Stop()\n    \n    // CleanupNow triggers an immediate cleanup cycle\n    CleanupNow(ctx context.Context) (CleanupResult, error)\n}\n\ntype CleanupResult struct {\n    AgentRuntimesCleaned   int\n    CodeInterpretersCleaned int\n    Errors                 []CleanupError\n}\n\ntype CleanupError struct {\n    ResourceKind string\n    Name         string\n    Namespace    string\n    Error        error\n}\n```\n\n### IdleTracker Interface\n\n```go\ntype IdleTracker interface {\n    // UpdateLastActivity updates the last activity timestamp for a resource\n    UpdateLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string, timestamp time.Time)\n    \n    // GetLastActivity retrieves the last activity timestamp\n    GetLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string) (time.Time, bool)\n    \n    // IsIdle checks if a resource is idle based on current time\n    IsIdle(kind, namespace, name string, timeout time.Duration) bool\n    \n    // Remove removes a resource from tracking\n    Remove(kind, namespace, name string)\n    \n    // ListIdleResources returns all idle resources exceeding timeout\n    ListIdleResources(timeout time.Duration) []ResourceKey\n}\n\ntype ResourceKey struct {\n    Kind      string\n    Namespace string\n    Name      string\n}\n```\n\n### Configuration\n\n```go\ntype CleanupConfig struct {\n    // AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout is the idle timeout for AgentRuntimes\n    AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout time.Duration\n    \n    // CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout is the idle timeout for CodeInterpreters\n    CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout time.Duration\n    \n    // CleanupInterval is how often to run cleanup cycles\n    CleanupInterval time.Duration\n    \n    // MaxConcurrentCleanups limits concurrent deletion operations\n    MaxConcurrentCleanups int\n    \n    // Enabled enables the idle cleanup controller\n    Enabled bool\n    \n    // DryRun enables dry-run mode (log only, no deletions)\n    DryRun bool\n    \n    // NamespaceAllowList restricts cleanup to specific namespaces (empty = all)\n    NamespaceAllowList []string\n    \n    // NamespaceDenyList excludes specific namespaces from cleanup\n    NamespaceDenyList []string\n}\n\nfunc DefaultCleanupConfig() *CleanupConfig {\n    return &CleanupConfig{\n        AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout:    30 * time.Minute,\n        CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout: 15 * time.Minute,\n        CleanupInterval:           5 * time.Minute,\n        MaxConcurrentCleanups:     10,\n        Enabled:                   true,\n        DryRun:                    false,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Metrics\n\n```go\ntype CleanupMetrics struct {\n    // agentRuntimeCleanupsTotal counts total AgentRuntime cleanups\n    agentRuntimeCleanupsTotal prometheus.Counter\n    \n    // codeInterpreterCleanupsTotal counts total CodeInterpreter cleanups\n    codeInterpreterCleanupsTotal prometheus.Counter\n    \n    // cleanupErrorsTotal counts cleanup errors by kind\n    cleanupErrorsTotal *prometheus.CounterVec\n    \n    // cleanupDurationSeconds tracks cleanup operation duration\n    cleanupDurationSeconds *prometheus.HistogramVec\n    \n    // idleResourcesDetected tracks detected idle resources\n    idleResourcesDetected *prometheus.GaugeVec\n}\n\nfunc (m *CleanupMetrics) RecordCleanup(kind string, duration time.Duration, err error)\nfunc (m *CleanupMetrics) SetIdleCount(kind string, count int)\nfunc (m *CleanupMetrics) RecordError(kind string)\n```\n\n### Idle Detection Logic\n\n```go\ntype idleTracker struct {\n    mu           sync.RWMutex\n    lastActivity map[ResourceKey]time.Time\n    logger       klog.Logger\n}\n\nfunc (t *idleTracker) UpdateLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string, timestamp time.Time) {\n    t.mu.Lock()\n    defer t.mu.Unlock()\n    \n    key := ResourceKey{Kind: kind, Namespace: namespace, Name: name}\n    t.lastActivity[key] = timestamp\n    \n    t.logger.V(4).Info(\"Updated last activity\",\n        \"kind\", kind,\n        \"namespace\", namespace,\n        \"name\", name,\n        \"timestamp\", timestamp)\n}\n\nfunc (t *idleTracker) IsIdle(kind, namespace, name string, timeout time.Duration) bool {\n    t.mu.RLock()\n    defer t.mu.RUnlock()\n    \n    key := ResourceKey{Kind: kind, Namespace: namespace, Name: name}\n    lastActivity, exists := t.lastActivity[key]\n    \n    if !exists {\n        // No activity recorded; use creation time as fallback\n        return true\n    }\n    \n    return time.Since(lastActivity) >= timeout\n}\n\nfunc (t *idleTracker) ListIdleResources(timeout time.Duration) []ResourceKey {\n    t.mu.RLock()\n    defer t.mu.RUnlock()\n    \n    now := time.Now()\n    var idle []ResourceKey\n    \n    for key, lastActivity := range t.lastActivity {\n        if now.Sub(lastActivity) >= timeout {\n            idle = append(idle, key)\n        }\n    }\n    \n    return idle\n}\n```\n\n### Cleanup Controller Implementation\n\n```go\ntype idleCleanupController struct {\n    config       *CleanupConfig\n    agentClient  versioned.Interface\n    idleTracker  IdleTracker\n    metrics      *CleanupMetrics\n    logger       klog.Logger\n    stopCh       chan struct{}\n    wg           sync.WaitGroup\n}\n\nfunc (c *idleCleanupController) Start(ctx context.Context) error {\n    if !c.config.Enabled {\n        c.logger.Info(\"Idle cleanup controller is disabled\")\n        return nil\n    }\n    \n    c.logger.Info(\"Starting idle cleanup controller\",\n        \"agentRuntimeTimeout\", c.config.AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout,\n        \"codeInterpreterTimeout\", c.config.CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout,\n        \"cleanupInterval\", c.config.CleanupInterval)\n    \n    // Start watch for resource status updates\n    c.wg.Add(1)\n    go func() {\n        defer c.wg.Done()\n        c.watchResources(ctx)\n    }()\n    \n    // Start periodic cleanup\n    c.wg.Add(1)\n    go func() {\n        defer c.wg.Done()\n        ticker := time.NewTicker(c.config.CleanupInterval)\n        defer ticker.Stop()\n        \n        for {\n            select {\n            case <-ctx.Done():\n                return\n            case <-c.stopCh:\n                return\n            case <-ticker.C:\n                c.runCleanup(ctx)\n            }\n        }\n    }()\n    \n    return nil\n}\n\nfunc (c *idleCleanupController) runCleanup(ctx context.Context) {\n    c.logger.V(4).Info(\"Starting cleanup cycle\")\n    \n    var g errgroup.Group\n    g.SetLimit(c.config.MaxConcurrentCleanups)\n    \n    // Clean idle AgentRuntimes\n    agentIdle := c.idleTracker.ListIdleResources(c.config.AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout)\n    c.metrics.SetIdleCount(\"AgentRuntime\", len(agentIdle))\n    \n    for _, key := range agentIdle {\n        if !c.isNamespaceAllowed(key.Namespace) {\n            continue\n        }\n        \n        g.Go(func() error {\n            return c.cleanupResource(ctx, key.Kind, key.Namespace, key.Name)\n        })\n    }\n    \n    // Clean idle CodeInterpreters\n    ciIdle := c.idleTracker.ListIdleResources(c.config.CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout)\n    c.metrics.SetIdleCount(\"CodeInterpreter\", len(ciIdle))\n    \n    for _, key := range ciIdle {\n        if !c.isNamespaceAllowed(key.Namespace) {\n            continue\n        }\n        \n        g.Go(func() error {\n            return c.cleanupResource(ctx, key.Kind, key.Namespace, key.Name)\n        })\n    }\n    \n    if err := g.Wait(); err != nil {\n        c.logger.Error(err, \"Cleanup cycle completed with errors\")\n    } else {\n        c.logger.V(4).Info(\"Cleanup cycle completed successfully\")\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (c *idleCleanupController) cleanupResource(ctx context.Context, kind, namespace, name string) error {\n    start := time.Now()\n    var err error\n    \n    if c.config.DryRun {\n        c.logger.Info(\"[DRY RUN] Would clean idle resource\",\n            \"kind\", kind,\n            \"namespace\", namespace,\n            \"name\", name)\n        c.metrics.RecordCleanup(kind, time.Since(start), nil)\n        return nil\n    }\n    \n    switch kind {\n    case \"AgentRuntime\":\n        err = c.agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete(\n            ctx, name, metav1.DeleteOptions{\n                GracePeriodSeconds: ptr.To(int64(30)),\n                PropagationPolicy:  ptr.To(metav1.DeletePropagationForeground),\n            })\n    case \"CodeInterpreter\":\n        err = c.agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete(\n            ctx, name, metav1.DeleteOptions{\n                GracePeriodSeconds: ptr.To(int64(30)),\n                PropagationPolicy:  ptr.To(metav1.DeletePropagationForeground),\n            })\n    default:\n        err = fmt.Errorf(\"unknown resource kind: %s\", kind)\n    }\n    \n    c.metrics.RecordCleanup(kind, time.Since(start), err)\n    \n    if err != nil {\n        c.logger.Error(err, \"Failed to cleanup idle resource\",\n            \"kind\", kind,\n            \"namespace\", namespace,\n            \"name\", name)\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    c.logger.Info(\"Cleaned up idle resource\",\n        \"kind\", kind,\n        \"namespace\", namespace,\n        \"name\", name)\n    \n    // Remove from idle tracker\n    c.idleTracker.Remove(kind, namespace, name)\n    \n    return nil\n}\n\nfunc (c *idleCleanupController) watchResources(ctx context.Context) {\n    // Watch AgentRuntimes\n    go c.watchAgentRuntimes(ctx)\n    \n    // Watch CodeInterpreters\n    go c.watchCodeInterpreters(ctx)\n    \n    <-ctx.Done()\n}\n\nfunc (c *idleCleanupController) watchAgentRuntimes(ctx context.Context) {\n    watcher, err := c.agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(metav1.NamespaceAll).Watch(\n        ctx, metav1.ListOptions{\n            TimeoutSeconds: ptr.To(int64(300)),\n        })\n    if err != nil {\n        c.logger.Error(err, \"Failed to watch AgentRuntimes\")\n        return\n    }\n    \n    for {\n        select {\n        case <-ctx.Done():\n            watcher.Stop()\n            return\n        case event, ok := <-watcher.ResultChan():\n            if !ok {\n                return\n            }\n            \n            ar, ok := event.Object.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n            if !ok {\n                continue\n            }\n            \n            key := ResourceKey{\n                Kind:      \"AgentRuntime\",\n                Namespace: ar.Namespace,\n                Name:      ar.Name,\n            }\n            \n            switch event.Type {\n            case watch.Added, watch.Modified:\n                // Update last activity from status.lastActivity or metadata.creationTimestamp\n                c.updateResourceActivity(key, ar.Status.LastActivityTime, ar.CreationTimestamp)\n            case watch.Deleted:\n                c.idleTracker.Remove(key.Kind, key.Namespace, key.Name)\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (c *idleCleanupController) watchCodeInterpreters(ctx context.Context) {\n    // Similar to watchAgentRuntimes but for CodeInterpreters\n    // ... implementation ...\n}\n\nfunc (c *idleCleanupController) updateResourceActivity(key ResourceKey, lastActivity, creation metav1.Time) {\n    if !lastActivity.IsZero() {\n        c.idleTracker.UpdateLastActivity(key.Kind, key.Namespace, key.Name, lastActivity.Time)\n    } else {\n        c.idleTracker.UpdateLastActivity(key.Kind, key.Namespace, key.Name, creation.Time)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (c *idleCleanupController) isNamespaceAllowed(namespace string) bool {\n    // Check deny list first\n    for _, denied := range c.config.NamespaceDenyList {\n        if namespace == denied {\n            return false\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // Check allow list\n    if len(c.config.NamespaceAllowList) == 0 {\n        return true\n    }\n    \n    for _, allowed := range c.config.NamespaceAllowList {\n        if namespace == allowed {\n            return true\n        }\n    }\n    \n    return false\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Reference\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `AGENTD_CLEANUP_ENABLED` | No | `true` | Enable/disable idle cleanup |\n| `AGENTD_CLEANUP_DRY_RUN` | No | `false` | Log only, no deletions |\n| `AGENTD_AGENT_RUNTIME_IDLE_TIMEOUT` | No | `30m` | AgentRuntime idle timeout |\n| `AGENTD_CODE_INTERPRETER_IDLE_TIMEOUT` | No | `15m` | CodeInterpreter idle timeout |\n| `AGENTD_CLEANUP_INTERVAL` | No | `5m` | Cleanup cycle interval |\n| `AGENTD_MAX_CONCURRENT_CLEANUPS` | No | `10` | Max concurrent deletions |\n| `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_ALLOW_LIST` | No | `` | Comma-separated allowed namespaces |\n| `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_DENY_LIST` | No | `kube-system,kube-public` | Comma-separated excluded namespaces |\n\n### Example Configuration\n\n```go\nconfig := &CleanupConfig{\n    AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout:    30 * time.Minute,\n    CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout: 15 * time.Minute,\n    CleanupInterval:           5 * time.Minute,\n    MaxConcurrentCleanups:     10,\n    Enabled:                   true,\n    DryRun:                    false,\n    NamespaceAllowList:        []string{\"default\", \"agent-workloads\"},\n    NamespaceDenyList:         []string{\"kube-system\", \"kube-public\", \"monitoring\"},\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Test | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `TestIdleTracker_UpdateLastActivity` | Verify activity timestamp updates |\n| `TestIdleTracker_IsIdle` | Test idle detection logic |\n| `TestIdleTracker_ListIdleResources` | Test listing idle resources |\n| `TestIdleTracker_Remove` | Test resource removal from tracking |\n| `TestCleanupController_runCleanup` | Test cleanup cycle logic |\n| `TestCleanupController_cleanupResource` | Test single resource cleanup |\n| `TestCleanupController_isNamespaceAllowed` | Test namespace filtering |\n| `TestCleanupController_DryRun` | Verify dry-run mode |\n| `TestCleanupMetrics_RecordCleanup` | Test metrics recording |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Test | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `TestIntegration_AgentRuntimeCleanup` | Full AgentRuntime cleanup flow |\n| `TestIntegration_CodeInterpreterCleanup` | Full CodeInterpreter cleanup flow |\n| `TestIntegration_ConcurrentCleanups` | Verify concurrent cleanup limits |\n| `TestIntegration_WatchReconnect` | Test watch reconnection on failure |\n| `TestIntegration_MetricsExposition` | Verify metrics are exposed correctly |\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```go\nfunc newFakeIdleCleanupController(t *testing.T) (*idleCleanupController, *fake.Clientset) {\n    fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n    config := DefaultCleanupConfig()\n    config.Enabled = true\n    config.DryRun = false\n    \n    tracker := &idleTracker{\n        lastActivity: make(map[ResourceKey]time.Time),\n        logger:       klog.Background(),\n    }\n    \n    metrics := NewCleanupMetrics(prometheus.NewRegistry())\n    \n    controller := &idleCleanupController{\n        config:       config,\n        agentClient:  fakeClient,\n        idleTracker:  tracker,\n        metrics:      metrics,\n        logger:       klog.Background(),\n        stopCh:       make(chan struct{}),\n    }\n    \n    return controller, fakeClient\n}\n\nfunc createTestAgentRuntime(namespace, name string) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime {\n    return &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      name,\n            Namespace: namespace,\n        },\n        Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n            Phase: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimePhaseRunning,\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `IdleCleanupController` interface implements all required methods\n- [ ] `IdleTracker` correctly tracks last activity timestamps\n- [ ] Idle detection works with configurable timeouts per resource type\n- [ ] Namespace allow/deny lists are respected\n- [ ] Dry-run mode logs without deleting\n- [ ] Concurrent cleanup limits are enforced\n- [ ] Metrics are exposed for monitoring\n- [ ] Watch reconnection handles connection failures\n- [ ] All unit tests pass\n- [ ] Integration tests pass with fake clients\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n- [ ] Documentation includes configuration examples\n- [ ] Graceful shutdown on controller stop\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### CleanupError Types\n\n```go\ntype CleanupErrorType string\n\nconst (\n    CleanupErrorNotFound      CleanupErrorType = \"not_found\"\n    CleanupErrorPermission    CleanupErrorType = \"permission_denied\"\n    CleanupErrorTimeout       CleanupErrorType = \"timeout\"\n    CleanupErrorConflict      CleanupErrorType = \"conflict\"\n    CleanupErrorUnknown       CleanupErrorType = \"unknown\"\n)\n\ntype CleanupError struct {\n    Type       CleanupErrorType\n    ResourceKind string\n    Namespace  string\n    Name       string\n    Message    string\n    Underlying error\n}\n\nfunc (e *CleanupError) Error() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"cleanup error [%s] for %s/%s/%s: %s\",\n        e.Type, e.ResourceKind, e.Namespace, e.Name, e.Message)\n}\n```\n\n### Error Conditions\n\n| Condition | Error Type | Handling | Description |\n|-----------|------------|----------|-------------|\n| Resource already deleted | `CleanupErrorNotFound` | Ignore | Resource was cleaned by another process |\n| Permission denied | `CleanupErrorPermission` | Log & retry | Insufficient RBAC permissions |\n| Deletion timeout | `CleanupErrorTimeout` | Log & retry | Resource deletion did not complete |\n| Finalizer conflict | `CleanupErrorConflict` | Log & skip | Resource has blocking finalizers |\n| Unknown API error | `CleanupErrorUnknown` | Log & retry | Uncategorized error |\n\n---\n\n## Future Considerations\n\n1. **Activity Webhooks**: Receive activity notifications from workload manager for precise idle detection\n2. **Graduated Timeouts**: Increase idle timeout for resources that are frequently recreated\n3. **Pre-Cleanup Notification**: Emit events before cleanup for user awareness\n4. **Resource-Specific Policies**: Allow per-resource idle timeout overrides via annotations\n5. **Cluster-Aware Scheduling**: Reduce cleanup frequency during high cluster load\n6. **Audit Logging**: Log all cleanup operations to audit trail\n7. **Custom Resource Conditions**: Add `IdleCleanupCandidate` condition to resources\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- AR-012: Sandbox Infrastructure\n- AR-016: PicoD File Management API\n- `deployment/client-go.md`: Kubernetes Client-Go Documentation\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/`: Workload Manager Reconciler\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`: AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter Types\n- Kubernetes Garbage Collection: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/architecture/garbage-collection/\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775862721385,"end":1775862721398}}}}
